reminiscence /ˌrɛmɪˈnɪsəns/

(reminiscences) 

1. N-VAR Someone's reminiscences are things that they remember from the past, and which they talk or write about. Reminiscence is the process of remembering these things and talking or writing about them. 回忆录; 缅怀往事的谈话 [正式] 

例： Here I am boring you with my reminiscences. 我的这些陈年老事让你烦了吧。

